definitions.definition: Any establishment where travellers can procure lodging , food , and drink .
One of the colleges (societies or buildings) in London, for students of the law barristers.
examples: the Inns of Court    the Inns of Chancery    Serjeants’ Inns

definitions.definition: The town residence of a nobleman or distinguished person.
A place of shelter; hence, dwelling , residence , abode .
